lines.value: <!friendster is an internet social network service
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: the friendster site was founded in mountain view california by jonathan abrams in 2002 and is privately owned
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: every user creates an online identity by filling out a questionnaire profile and uploading a user picture and then defines a gallery of friends and the service then integrates these galleries allowing a user to search through a list of their friends their friends friends and so on
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: the premise is that in this way one can interact with and meet people who are always a friend of a friend of a friend and not a random unknown person such as may be found on instant messaging or irc
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: it is difficult to verify the number of members or active members of friendster
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: currently the service's home page claims more than 19 million profiles photos and blogs and an info page states that there are more than 20 million members
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: in the press however an often cited figure is approximately 2 million
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: if user id numbers are assigned consecutively there have been at least 21351560 though it is unclear what proportion of unique id numbers represent unique active users
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: friendster is based on the circle of friends technique for networking individuals in virtual communities and demonstrates the small world phenomenon
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: it was significantly influenced by ryze a business networking site founded in 2001 where friendster's founder was an early member
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: of course as with any form of social network online there are also members who are not who they claim to be
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: a significant number of people have created new profiles for bands movie television and book characters and activist groups as a form of online fan club
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: these accounts are often referred to as fakesters
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: while the administrators of the site at first tried to discourage the practice as the service became more popular official fakesters were created by the friendster staff to correspond with television and movie characters
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: the website is no longer running as a beta test
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: the slow response time that plagued the site in its early stages seems to have abated
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: this is partly attributed to a rewrite and conversion of the site's webpages from jsp via jakarta tomcat to php around july 2004
lines.name: Chuvash

lines.value: at the time of the conversion many people debated whether this proved that scalability of php was better than jsp
